label: 4AD
description:
Widening the aspect ratio and raising the budget, Portuguese-Danish prodigy Erika de Casier retains her tight grip on R&B nostalgia with 'Still', simultaneously poking around reggaetón and PinkPantheress-style soft jungle. It's more effortlessly intimate, club-friendly gear that'll be haunting ur mind long after it's finished - featuring guest spots from Shygirl, Blood Orange and They Hate Change.

label: SFX
description:
Klahrk's latest for Zoë Mc Pherson and Alessandra Leone's SFX imprint is a void-melting set of obsessively-tweaked, sound design-fwd dancefloor rollers, peak gear for anyone bored with club nostalgia or minimal repetition. Features remixes from CRRDR and Bell Curve.

If you heard Klahrk's 2021-released 'Oscillate and Shimmer', or his follow-up collaboration with KAVARI, then you'll already have a good idea where this one's going. 'Blistering' refines and expertly sculpts the formula, curving... more

description:
Producer to rap royalty and the ATL new skool, Brodinski meets noisy beat slugger Qoso on a batch of raw knuckled reggaeton and abstracted rap instrumentals 

Studded by Modulaw’s co-productions and guest vocal features from Albany, Yung Beef, YMN Gus, Retro 1312 & Zaky, ’Aurora’ racks up seven club-toned sidespins on tresillo styles and patterns that knit the current underground rhizome.
